- Code quality (Task 1, reactive BT nodes): Approve. Observed minor duplication between `ReactiveSelectorNode` and `ReactiveSequenceNode` that mirrors the existing selector/sequence split; noted for future factoring if a third variant lands.
- Code quality (Task 2, clearRunningState): Approve. Flagged that `readonly` was removed from `BTNode.index` / `nodeCount` to enable the reindex pass. An alternative recursive-walk implementation would preserve `readonly` but trades cache locality; the current design is acceptable for typical BT sizes.
- Code quality (Task 3, semantic diffMode): Approve. Suggested lifecycle test combining set ƒ+' clearDirty ƒ+' set-identical ƒ+' clearDirty ƒ+' set-different as future hardening; not a blocker.
